WEBVTT

00:02.970 --> 00:04.071
Previously on Graceland...

00:04.104 --> 00:05.405
- Easy, Mike, Mike, Mike, Mike.
- [groaning]

00:05.439 --> 00:07.040
Just let the pain pass.

00:07.074 --> 00:08.075
Breathe, brother.

00:09.309 --> 00:10.277
I can't let you do this.

00:10.310 --> 00:12.446
God damn it, Mike!

00:12.479 --> 00:14.882
You have to stop trying
to save me!

00:14.915 --> 00:16.884
I'm moving out.

00:16.917 --> 00:18.485
Are you police?

00:18.519 --> 00:19.653
Amber, please.

00:19.686 --> 00:21.655
- I'm pregnant.
- Not in the stomach.

00:21.688 --> 00:22.856
Stupid--

00:22.890 --> 00:24.791
None of us want an indictment.

00:24.825 --> 00:26.093
What's it gonna
cost me, boss?

00:26.126 --> 00:27.594
Ari Adamian.

00:27.628 --> 00:29.396
He's a lieutenant
in the Sarkissian family.

00:29.429 --> 00:30.464
You took his kidney.

00:30.497 --> 00:31.832
Kidneys.

00:33.934 --> 00:36.103
There was no cover team.
No one was listening.

00:36.136 --> 00:37.704
You hung me out to dry, man.

00:37.738 --> 00:40.908
It is not over
until it is over.

00:40.941 --> 00:43.310
Somebody has to be held
accountable for Ari's crimes.

00:43.343 --> 00:44.678
I'll be their sin eater.

00:44.711 --> 00:46.280
- Johnny!
- Hey! Hey!

00:46.313 --> 00:48.448
Lucia stays
and the money flows.

00:48.482 --> 00:50.284
This is your fate, Johnny.

00:50.317 --> 00:53.353
It's time to own it.

00:57.157 --> 00:58.392
(Charlie) Don't wake him.
(Jakes) I bet he knows.

00:58.425 --> 01:00.227
Dale, he's sleep--
Dale!

01:00.260 --> 01:01.562
(Jakes)
Sleeping Beauty?

01:01.595 --> 01:04.631
[snoring]
Mm!

01:04.665 --> 01:06.700
Can you tie a bow tie?

01:06.733 --> 01:09.002
What?

01:10.771 --> 01:12.940
A bow tie.
Can you tie one?

01:12.973 --> 01:14.408
I can tie a regular tie.

01:14.441 --> 01:16.543
Yeah, you and everybody else.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.879
It's not a special...thing.

01:18.912 --> 01:20.380
Why are you harassing me?

01:20.414 --> 01:21.648
Why are you sleeping
on the couch?

01:21.682 --> 01:22.649
Don't you got a room?

01:22.683 --> 01:24.084
Yes.

01:24.117 --> 01:25.218
(Charlie)
Morning, Mikey.

01:25.252 --> 01:27.421
Stairs give you
some trouble last night?

01:27.454 --> 01:28.689
Yeah.
Flat ground's fine,

01:28.722 --> 01:30.023
but the whole
foot over foot thing,

01:30.057 --> 01:32.292
I don't know how you
guys do it.

01:33.527 --> 01:34.728
What's with the dress up?

01:34.761 --> 01:36.863
DOJ's giving Paige
her big award.

01:36.897 --> 01:38.632
That's today?

01:38.665 --> 01:39.967
Yep, that's today.
You comin'?

01:40.000 --> 01:42.135
Yeah.
Hey...

01:42.169 --> 01:43.670
Johnny knows how
to tie a bow tie.

01:43.704 --> 01:45.572
That'd be great
if Johnny was home.

01:45.606 --> 01:46.707
He didn't come home
last night?

01:46.740 --> 01:48.342
No, and with Sid
gunning for us,

01:48.375 --> 01:49.476
I was under
the impression that

01:49.509 --> 01:51.511
sleeping at Graceland
wasn't optional.

01:51.545 --> 01:53.280
(Briggs)
Everything's optional, DJ.

01:53.313 --> 01:56.550
It's all just a matter of
reconceiving one's parameters.

01:56.583 --> 01:57.951
Thank you, Confucius.

01:57.985 --> 01:59.953
I'll remember that next time
I'm being assassinated.

01:59.987 --> 02:02.422
That's my coffee.

02:02.456 --> 02:05.158
I brought you a suit, Mikey.
Saved you a trip up Everest.

02:05.192 --> 02:07.494
- Thanks.
- You all right?

02:07.527 --> 02:08.562
Yeah.
First rate, Chuck.

02:08.595 --> 02:10.497
(Mike)
First rate, huh?

02:10.530 --> 02:13.166
What about the Armenian-
flavored sin eating?

02:13.200 --> 02:15.168
It's a new day, Warren.

02:18.138 --> 02:19.806
"It's a new day, Warren"?

02:19.840 --> 02:21.475
That cannot be good.

02:21.508 --> 02:22.976
No.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.614
(Priest)
And Jesus said unto Peter,

02:27.648 --> 02:29.783
"Flesh and blood
has not revealed it,

02:29.816 --> 02:32.586
"but my Father which
is in heaven.

02:32.619 --> 02:34.521
"And I also say to thee,

02:34.554 --> 02:38.525
"upon this rock
I will build my church,

02:38.558 --> 02:41.528
"and the gates of hell
shall not prevail against it.

02:41.561 --> 02:44.965
"And I will give unto thee

02:44.998 --> 02:48.068
"the keys of
the kingdom of heaven.

02:48.101 --> 02:52.406
"And whatsoever
thou shalt bind on earth

02:52.439 --> 02:54.775
"shall be bound in heaven.

02:54.808 --> 02:56.043
"And whatsoever...

02:56.076 --> 02:58.445
"thou shall lose on earth

02:58.478 --> 03:01.782
shall be lost in heaven."

03:16.563 --> 03:20.333
Is this Carlito's passage
or yours?

03:20.367 --> 03:23.503
Why the hell would I have
a tunnel to Mexico, man?

03:23.537 --> 03:25.939
Once we get on the other side,
how do we get to the compound?

03:25.972 --> 03:27.407
Oh, "we" nothing.

03:27.441 --> 03:28.975
Homeland's looking for you
at the border crossing.

03:29.009 --> 03:31.011
This is your best option.

03:32.612 --> 03:34.014
[throws switch]

03:34.047 --> 03:38.518
[lights buzzing]

03:38.552 --> 03:40.353
After you, Blair.

03:40.387 --> 03:43.390
Ha-ha, no, I don't think so.

03:46.560 --> 03:51.331
(DOJ Speaker)
How do we judge
a person's character?

03:51.364 --> 03:54.167
We could say that goodness
is a product of good intentions.

03:54.201 --> 03:57.971
That it's enough
to simply mean well.

03:58.004 --> 04:02.409
We could argue that thoughts are
the greater part of conduct.

04:02.442 --> 04:05.879
But I think we should insist
upon measuring a person

04:05.912 --> 04:08.381
by their deeds...

04:08.415 --> 04:11.952
By the goodness or badness of
their self-determined actions.

04:11.985 --> 04:14.921
For the vast majority of us,
if reckoning were to come today,

04:14.955 --> 04:18.358
we'd find ourselves
woefully short of action,

04:18.391 --> 04:20.327
that, despite
our best intentions,

04:20.360 --> 04:23.663
the world is no better off
with us in it.

04:23.697 --> 04:26.133
But for our undercover agents
in the field,

04:26.166 --> 04:27.701
deeds are currency,

04:27.734 --> 04:31.371
and action is
the state of play.

04:31.404 --> 04:34.407
They're foot soldiers
in the fight for justice.

04:36.176 --> 04:40.914
And the best of them are what
we see when we imagine heroes.

04:40.947 --> 04:42.749
Ladies and gentlemen,

04:42.783 --> 04:45.919
today the office of the Attorney
General is proud to present

04:45.952 --> 04:48.889
DEA Agent Paige Arkin

04:48.922 --> 04:51.124
with the Award for
Exceptional Heroism.

04:51.158 --> 04:57.164
[applause]

05:15.715 --> 05:17.184
Thank you.

05:17.217 --> 05:21.221
[scattered applause]

05:23.790 --> 05:26.760
[dance music]

05:26.793 --> 05:34.801
♪ ♪

05:37.604 --> 05:39.706
I'll grab us
a couple beers.

05:41.107 --> 05:43.410
The money's in pesos.

05:44.811 --> 05:46.913
Is this where your girlfriend
works or what?

05:46.947 --> 05:48.949
That's funny, man.

05:48.982 --> 05:50.650
We're supposed
to wait here?

05:50.684 --> 05:52.185
Yeah.

05:52.219 --> 05:54.054
Enjoy yourself, Sid.

05:54.087 --> 05:56.590
It's gonna be a long day.

05:58.992 --> 06:01.962
[electronic music]

06:01.995 --> 06:08.134
♪ ♪

06:15.976 --> 06:18.111
♪ ♪

06:18.144 --> 06:19.713
- Congratulations.
- Thanks.

06:19.746 --> 06:22.349
(woman)
Honored to meet you.

06:22.382 --> 06:24.651
Well, if it isn't
our exceptional hero.

06:24.684 --> 06:25.952
- Hey, guys.
- Let me see it.

06:25.986 --> 06:28.822
Let me see the hardware.

06:30.891 --> 06:32.459
That's nice.
Nice, right?

06:32.492 --> 06:33.760
Beautiful.

06:33.793 --> 06:34.761
It's a good thing
they weren't giving out

06:34.794 --> 06:36.596
an award for exceptional
public speaking.

06:36.630 --> 06:38.832
- Can you write my next speech?
- Stop.

06:38.865 --> 06:40.834
The only reason this exists
is for a photo-op.

06:40.867 --> 06:42.369
It's--it's just
a piece of metal.

06:42.402 --> 06:43.603
Okay.

06:43.637 --> 06:44.871
Hey, come on,
you're killing me.

06:44.905 --> 06:47.173
There's 7.3 billion people
out there

06:47.207 --> 06:49.009
who will never get
that piece of metal

06:49.042 --> 06:52.612
because they didn't save a bunch
of girls from sex slavery.

06:52.646 --> 06:55.148
No?
I'll get the car.

06:55.181 --> 06:56.816
Can you talk some sense
into her, please?

06:56.850 --> 06:59.619
He's right, you know.
What do I say?

06:59.653 --> 07:00.620
Don't.

07:00.654 --> 07:03.823
Come on.
What do I always say?

07:04.858 --> 07:06.192
Bitches get shit done.

07:06.226 --> 07:07.560
Damn right,
bitches get shit done.

07:07.594 --> 07:08.995
Give me some.

07:09.029 --> 07:12.632
Paige, you can't leave me
in that house all alone.

07:12.666 --> 07:15.035
The genital ratio's
already way out of whack.

07:15.068 --> 07:16.303
Shut up.

07:16.336 --> 07:18.138
[cell phone ringing]

07:18.171 --> 07:19.639
I gotta take this.

07:19.673 --> 07:21.041
I'm gonna throw you
a dinner tonight.

07:21.074 --> 07:23.243
We're not done here.

07:23.276 --> 07:24.744
Hello?

07:26.746 --> 07:28.915
Can we talk?

07:33.386 --> 07:34.821
No.

07:39.559 --> 07:40.627
Are you kidding me?

07:40.660 --> 07:42.896
My psychic aunt could
give me more than that.

07:42.929 --> 07:45.765
No, it's okay.
Yeah, thank you.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.968
Mm-hmm.
Shit.

07:48.001 --> 07:49.035
Interpol?

07:49.069 --> 07:50.503
Yeah, they got
jack on Germaine.

07:50.537 --> 07:52.572
A record, some financials,
but it's all a decade old.

07:52.605 --> 07:54.607
- It's useless.
- Yeah.

07:54.641 --> 07:56.209
Well, you could still roll
through the DA,

07:56.242 --> 07:57.811
have him work up
a deal for Amber.

07:57.844 --> 07:59.312
We went through this.

07:59.346 --> 08:01.214
I ain't giving her shit.

08:01.247 --> 08:02.449
It's not about what
you give her, Charlie.

08:02.482 --> 08:03.650
It's about
what she gives you.

08:03.683 --> 08:05.452
Yeah, well, she almost
gave me a miscarriage.

08:05.485 --> 08:06.753
In infinite universes,

08:06.786 --> 08:08.955
there is not one
in which I let her walk.

08:08.989 --> 08:11.291
Who said anything
about walking?

08:11.324 --> 08:14.527
Knock it down
to ten and six.

08:14.561 --> 08:16.896
If you don't want to do it,
I get it.

08:16.930 --> 08:19.132
But sometimes we're only left
with unpalatable measures.

08:19.165 --> 08:21.134
You know?

08:22.135 --> 08:23.303
Yeah.

08:23.336 --> 08:26.306
[moody electronic music]

08:26.339 --> 08:34.347
♪ ♪

08:36.016 --> 08:39.185
Careful with
that stuff, Mike.

08:39.219 --> 08:41.321
I know, it's just...
more pain than I thought.

08:41.354 --> 08:42.455
Mm-hmm.

08:42.489 --> 08:43.623
Well, then maybe
you should be resting

08:43.656 --> 08:45.658
in a hospital bed
instead of counting oxy

08:45.692 --> 08:47.660
on our communal
coffee table.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.696
[exhales]

08:49.729 --> 08:52.132
- Hey, Briggs?
- Yeah?

08:52.165 --> 08:55.502
Do you really think you have
Ari Adamian under control?

08:55.535 --> 08:57.170
[exhales]
You know,

08:57.203 --> 08:58.872
you can't control
a psychopath any more

08:58.905 --> 09:01.941
then you can the break
of a swell, so,

09:01.975 --> 09:03.443
for now I'm surfing.

09:03.476 --> 09:06.946
Then why don't you explain
"It's a new day, Warren"?

09:06.980 --> 09:09.349
Some things broken
can't be fixed.

09:09.382 --> 09:11.384
[sighs]

09:13.753 --> 09:15.488
What are you planning?

09:15.522 --> 09:17.757
Well, Logan won't let me
put Ari away,

09:17.791 --> 09:19.159
so I'm gonna
put him down.

09:19.192 --> 09:21.094
[scoffs]

09:23.263 --> 09:24.464
You're serious.

09:24.497 --> 09:26.433
With Ari dead,
Logan continues to squeeze me,

09:26.466 --> 09:27.434
I'll take a reassignment.

09:27.467 --> 09:29.102
Logan is gonna know
it was you.

09:29.135 --> 09:30.270
Ari's got a lot
of enemies, Mike.

09:30.303 --> 09:31.838
The Bureau
will be watching.

09:31.871 --> 09:33.440
They won't, actually.

09:33.473 --> 09:35.141
By Logan's design,
dick that he is,

09:35.175 --> 09:36.376
I have no cover team.

09:36.409 --> 09:38.611
So, when I'm alone with Ari,
I am alone with him.

09:38.645 --> 09:39.846
Okay, Logan is
not gonna accept

09:39.879 --> 09:41.948
this convenient death
as your out.

09:41.981 --> 09:43.316
If you don't do
exactly what he says,

09:43.349 --> 09:46.219
he's gonna use that
Juan Badillo tape against you.

09:47.854 --> 09:50.523
It was in my bag.

09:50.557 --> 09:51.758
If Logan has something
against you,

09:51.791 --> 09:53.460
it's gotta be Juan's death.

09:53.493 --> 09:55.595
I am already on the hook for
one Ari Adamian murder, Mike.

09:55.628 --> 09:56.863
[phone vibrating]

09:56.896 --> 09:59.032
In a few months, I'll be
drowning in felonies.

09:59.065 --> 10:01.835
I'll take my chances with
that tape, thank you very much.

10:01.868 --> 10:04.104
It's Ari.

10:04.137 --> 10:05.505
This is not gonna end well.

10:05.538 --> 10:07.707
No. That part was
never up to me.

10:07.740 --> 10:11.010
What I can control is
how it doesn't end well.

10:11.044 --> 10:12.245
Watch yourself with
that stuff, man.

10:12.278 --> 10:13.947
Really.
It's dangerous.

10:13.980 --> 10:15.982
- Huh?
- Mm-hmm.

10:19.252 --> 10:22.222
[Mexican hip hop music]

10:22.255 --> 10:26.759
♪ ♪

10:26.793 --> 10:28.461
I was visiting
Uncle Tev.

10:28.495 --> 10:30.730
Yesterday, he looked
like dead fish.

10:30.763 --> 10:34.901
Today...the shark is back.

10:34.934 --> 10:36.836
That kidney's kicking up.

10:36.870 --> 10:39.139
Oh yeah, he's pinching
nurses' asses,

10:39.172 --> 10:41.541
joking like it's his birthday.

10:41.574 --> 10:44.310
By the end of the week,
he'll be dancing the kochari.

10:44.344 --> 10:48.114
(Briggs)
Well, next week's
a long way off, Ari.

10:48.148 --> 10:51.451
[laughs]
Look at this fat boy.

10:51.484 --> 10:54.587
Someone need to tell him you
can't outrun an ass that big.

10:54.621 --> 10:55.622
Well, you know,

10:55.655 --> 10:58.124
nothing ever got solved
by apathy, right?

10:58.158 --> 11:00.460
You say some queer shit, Guy.

11:00.493 --> 11:01.728
But you're not wrong.

11:01.761 --> 11:04.430
[laughs]
Hey.

11:04.464 --> 11:06.733
(Briggs)
Ari, what are you--

11:06.766 --> 11:08.234
- Jesus Christ.
- Chester Cheeto!

11:08.268 --> 11:10.403
Really, you're gonna
run like that, huh?

11:10.436 --> 11:11.704
[grunting]

11:11.738 --> 11:13.173
Ari! Ari, hey, hey, hey--

11:13.206 --> 11:15.909
Ari, Ari, Ari, relax!
Relax! Ugh--

11:15.942 --> 11:18.378
I am relaxed.
Hey, Guy!

11:18.411 --> 11:19.846
This is Ty Gillibrand.

11:19.879 --> 11:22.182
His friends call him Gilly,
but I call him Chester Cheeto.

11:22.215 --> 11:23.983
- You know why?
- I have no idea.

11:24.017 --> 11:25.818
'Cause he's
a Chester Cheeto-eating

11:25.852 --> 11:27.453
son-of-a-bitch,
aren't you?

11:27.487 --> 11:29.722
What have you got in here, huh?
Originals or puffs?

11:29.756 --> 11:32.692
- Leave me alone!
- Leave you alone? Ha!

11:32.725 --> 11:33.927
I'll leave you alone,

11:33.960 --> 11:37.130
when you lick the Cheetos
off your fat fingers

11:37.163 --> 11:39.032
and sign the freaking paper
like you promised, okay?

11:39.065 --> 11:40.700
I didn't promise anything!

11:40.733 --> 11:41.801
- There you go.
- You and your homeboy

11:41.834 --> 11:43.002
can rough me up,

11:43.036 --> 11:46.005
but I'm not selling
to the Sarkissians.

11:47.774 --> 11:48.975
Man, why'd you do that?

11:49.008 --> 11:50.176
- Ow!
- Huh?

11:50.210 --> 11:51.811
- What are you do--
Ow, Ari, I don't--

11:51.844 --> 11:52.979
You don't disparage
my family!

11:53.012 --> 11:53.980
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

11:54.013 --> 11:55.848
[overlapping yelling]

11:55.882 --> 11:58.384
That's a violation!
Do you understand?

11:58.418 --> 12:00.253
- Yes!
- You understand me?

12:00.286 --> 12:01.354
- Yes!
- Yes?

12:01.387 --> 12:02.522
- Yes! Let me up!
- Is that good, Guy?

12:02.555 --> 12:04.390
I think we should
pull him up, Ari.

12:04.424 --> 12:05.625
Yes, pull me up,
pull me up!

12:05.658 --> 12:07.126
No, I think I don't trust you!

12:07.160 --> 12:09.596
I think you sign
the contracts like that!

12:09.629 --> 12:10.830
- What?
- What?

12:10.863 --> 12:13.132
Yes. You hold him.
Hold him.

12:13.166 --> 12:14.467
[struggling]

12:14.500 --> 12:15.868
(Gillibrand)
No!

12:15.902 --> 12:17.737
- Freakin' where's my pen?
- For God's sakes!

12:17.770 --> 12:19.539
There you are.
Okay.

12:19.572 --> 12:20.673
Give it to me!

12:20.707 --> 12:22.942
There you go, fat boy.

12:22.976 --> 12:25.044
- There you go.
- Give me the contract!

12:25.078 --> 12:27.013
Take your pen.

12:27.046 --> 12:28.147
Don't forget to date it.

12:28.181 --> 12:29.515
What is it?
What's the date?

12:29.549 --> 12:31.184
It's June 10th, man,
it's June 10th.

12:31.217 --> 12:32.919
- Sign it, Chester, come on.
- Uh-huh.

12:32.952 --> 12:33.920
(Ari)
It's triplicate.

12:33.953 --> 12:35.021
(Gillibrand)
Shit!

12:35.054 --> 12:36.155
- [grunts]
- Each page.

12:36.189 --> 12:37.890
- [struggling]
- And initial at the top.

12:37.924 --> 12:39.492
- Initial at the top.
- Ari, he's slipping, man.

12:39.525 --> 12:40.526
- Come on.
- All right!

12:40.560 --> 12:41.527
Oh, my God, here!
Here!

12:41.561 --> 12:43.129
- [struggling]
- Let me up!

12:43.162 --> 12:44.330
No!

12:44.364 --> 12:46.165
[screaming]

12:46.199 --> 12:47.800
[thuds]

12:48.768 --> 12:50.770
You drop him?

12:50.803 --> 12:52.005
He was too heavy.

12:52.038 --> 12:54.874
You freakin' drop
Chester Cheeto off a bridge?

12:54.907 --> 12:56.442
- We gotta go down there, man.
- No, Guy, it's fine, he sign.

12:56.476 --> 12:58.044
Look, he sign all three.

12:58.077 --> 13:00.013
This one's a little messy,
but I think it's still binding.

13:00.046 --> 13:01.080
(Gillibrand)
Help me! Help me!

13:01.114 --> 13:03.950
I can't move!
Help! Help!

13:03.983 --> 13:06.419
[chuckling]
Look at that.

13:06.452 --> 13:09.656
Saved by his fatness.

13:09.689 --> 13:10.790
We gotta go
help him, Ari.

13:10.823 --> 13:11.924
No, Guy,
we gotta go.

13:11.958 --> 13:12.959
Look at all these people.

13:12.992 --> 13:15.928
Someone called 9-11.
Come on.

13:26.005 --> 13:30.243
♪ ♪

13:30.276 --> 13:32.011
[scoffs]
No.

13:32.045 --> 13:33.980
Orange ain't your color,
sweetheart.

13:34.013 --> 13:37.550
No, no, no way.
Screw you.

13:37.583 --> 13:38.885
Take me back.
Screw this.

13:38.918 --> 13:41.421
Sit down, Amber.

13:46.559 --> 13:47.694
If you think you're
gonna talk me out of

13:47.727 --> 13:49.329
the entrapment charges,
you can think again.

13:49.362 --> 13:51.230
Entrapment, huh?

13:51.264 --> 13:52.665
(Amber)
Yeah.

13:52.699 --> 13:55.234
I wasn't gonna rob a bank
until you waltzed in.

13:55.268 --> 13:58.204
You kidnapped
a federal agent, dummy.

13:58.237 --> 13:59.405
You crashed my car

13:59.439 --> 14:02.375
and let that British nutjob
beat the shit out of me.

14:02.408 --> 14:05.478
I was protecting you from him,
you bitch.

14:05.511 --> 14:07.680
[scoffs]

14:07.714 --> 14:09.382
You and your baby.

14:09.415 --> 14:10.883
If you knew I was a Fed,

14:10.917 --> 14:12.418
you'd have put the bullet
in me yourself.

14:12.452 --> 14:14.120
Say otherwise.

14:19.559 --> 14:22.962
I would have put it
right in your belly.

14:27.233 --> 14:29.068
This ain't happening.

14:30.169 --> 14:31.671
Send this animal back
to her cage.

14:31.704 --> 14:32.739
No deal.

14:32.772 --> 14:33.740
What deal?

14:33.773 --> 14:35.908
[door unlocks
and buzzes]

14:35.942 --> 14:38.277
Wait.

14:38.311 --> 14:41.614
What deal?

14:46.252 --> 14:49.021
I want Germaine.

14:50.089 --> 14:52.892
Fine.

14:52.925 --> 14:54.227
What do I get?

14:54.260 --> 14:55.561
Ten, chance of six.

14:55.595 --> 14:58.831
- Probation?
- Forever.

14:58.865 --> 15:02.435
You're headed for
Federal pen, baby girl.

15:02.468 --> 15:04.003
Flagged for Supermax.

15:04.036 --> 15:06.739
You could rot in that cell
or you can give me Germaine.

15:08.875 --> 15:11.911
[exhales]
I don't know where he is.

15:11.944 --> 15:15.481
Listen to me,
I don't know where he is.

15:15.515 --> 15:17.183
All right, but I know
a guy in south Florida.

15:17.216 --> 15:19.886
He's a dealer.
[sighs]

15:19.919 --> 15:21.954
Germaine cleans his cash.

15:21.988 --> 15:23.322
How do you know?

15:23.356 --> 15:27.360
We met at a party
Germaine had on a yacht.

15:27.393 --> 15:29.128
We went back to his after.

15:29.162 --> 15:32.031
Where's that, Amber?

15:32.064 --> 15:34.300
I don't remember.

15:34.333 --> 15:36.669
But if you bring me to Miami,
and get me back to where we met,

15:36.702 --> 15:39.272
I think I could track us
back to his place.

15:39.305 --> 15:40.840
And I could make
an introduction for you.

15:40.873 --> 15:43.242
No way.

15:43.276 --> 15:44.544
Well, we're both
out of options,

15:44.577 --> 15:46.946
so you can stop acting like
Godzilla with tits.

15:48.481 --> 15:51.284
You want Germaine,
this is how it works.

15:52.585 --> 15:55.555
[rock music]

15:55.588 --> 16:01.194
♪ ♪

16:01.227 --> 16:02.595
Agent Warren.

16:02.628 --> 16:05.264
Good to see
you're feeling better.

16:05.298 --> 16:09.502
"Justice is incidental
to law and order."

16:09.535 --> 16:10.503
Excuse me?

16:10.536 --> 16:13.706
Hoover said that.

16:13.739 --> 16:16.409
Of course, when he died,

16:16.442 --> 16:19.779
they found out that he'd been
blackmailing senators for years.

16:22.982 --> 16:25.351
I know Paul Briggs.

16:25.384 --> 16:27.687
I know what he's capable of.

16:27.720 --> 16:30.723
And you need to stop what you're
doing before this goes too far.

16:32.124 --> 16:33.259
Perhaps you're unaware,

16:33.292 --> 16:36.629
but this is wildly
inappropriate behavior.

16:36.662 --> 16:40.466
Perhaps you're unaware...

16:40.500 --> 16:44.036
I used to work for
the Deputy Director.

16:44.070 --> 16:46.138
I make one phone call

16:46.172 --> 16:48.941
and Washington knows exactly
what's happening here.

16:54.614 --> 16:58.985
Believe it or not, I am
familiar with your work history.

16:59.018 --> 17:02.822
But before you place a call
to the J. Edgar Hoover Building,

17:02.855 --> 17:05.825
let's refresh ourselves.

17:05.858 --> 17:07.026
Since Quantico,

17:07.059 --> 17:10.062
you have managed to fail
both upward and downward

17:10.096 --> 17:13.099
by virtue of a nonexistent
arrest record.

17:13.132 --> 17:14.901
I took down
Jeremiah Bello.

17:14.934 --> 17:17.136
No, Bello was arrested while you
were bleeding out on the floor.

17:17.169 --> 17:20.306
- It was my case.
- Shut up, Agent Warren!

17:20.339 --> 17:22.208
Your investigations
have manifested

17:22.241 --> 17:26.746
an almost entirely
unprecedented fatality rate.

17:26.779 --> 17:30.683
Truly, I've never seen
anything like it.

17:30.716 --> 17:35.254
By any metric, those cases
have been failures.

17:35.288 --> 17:39.191
So do you genuinely believe

17:39.225 --> 17:42.461
the Deputy Director
is taking your calls?

17:46.933 --> 17:49.902
Go home, Agent Warren.

17:52.705 --> 17:54.307
Worry about yourself.

17:56.876 --> 17:59.845
[hip hop music]

17:59.879 --> 18:06.485
♪ ♪

18:06.519 --> 18:09.689
Hey, let me ask you
a question, man.

18:09.722 --> 18:12.124
How is Carlito not
the last person on Earth

18:12.158 --> 18:14.126
you want to see right now?

18:14.160 --> 18:15.861
Now, he already got me.

18:15.895 --> 18:18.598
What does he need
a dirty cop for?

18:18.631 --> 18:21.400
My deal with Carlito
is done.

18:21.434 --> 18:23.202
I've already executed
my end.

18:23.235 --> 18:26.906
Yeah, you mean
killing his pops, right?

18:26.939 --> 18:29.809
You and your little
21 Jump Street buddies

18:29.842 --> 18:33.112
stole a lot of my money.

18:33.145 --> 18:34.947
Carlos Senior probably
would've let me work it off

18:34.981 --> 18:37.617
but I don't have ten more years
of good luck in me.

18:37.650 --> 18:39.085
And I'm betting Carlito
probably told you

18:39.118 --> 18:40.753
he'd pay you all in
one lump sum, huh?

18:40.786 --> 18:42.355
You're a genius.

18:42.388 --> 18:44.690
I'll give you one thing,
Sid, man, you...

18:44.724 --> 18:46.892
You're a hell of
an optimist, bro.

18:46.926 --> 18:50.563
'Cause if this shit was me,

18:50.596 --> 18:53.065
and I was doin'
the numbers in my head,

18:53.099 --> 18:55.001
think I'd realize giving you
a bullet to the head's

18:55.034 --> 18:56.569
a lot cheaper than
giving you a payday,

18:56.602 --> 18:58.604
but that's just me.

19:03.976 --> 19:06.412
It's about that time.
Let's go.

19:06.445 --> 19:08.347
Carlito wanted me dead,

19:08.381 --> 19:10.282
he'd have had you do
the job up north.

19:10.316 --> 19:12.418
Yeah, maybe,
but, uh...

19:12.451 --> 19:15.154
I ain't a killer.

19:18.658 --> 19:19.825
You know, there's
no reason for me

19:19.859 --> 19:21.260
to buy any of your concerns.

19:21.293 --> 19:24.597
I don't give a shit about you
buying my concern, man.

19:26.132 --> 19:27.566
I'm not saying this
'cause I care about you.

19:27.600 --> 19:31.837
I'm saying it 'cause...

19:31.871 --> 19:34.674
I need to make a deal.

19:34.707 --> 19:37.009
You help me and Lucia,
I'll help you get your money.

19:37.043 --> 19:39.211
Wow, must be a special bit
of Mexican cooch.

19:39.245 --> 19:40.413
Stay the hell--

19:40.446 --> 19:43.783
Hey--
Hey, easy.

19:43.816 --> 19:46.318
[whispering]
Tough guy.

19:46.352 --> 19:48.954
He's here.

19:48.988 --> 19:50.956
You know who that is, man?

19:50.990 --> 19:52.858
(Tuturro)
That's Flaco.

19:52.892 --> 19:54.527
He don't deliver money.

19:54.560 --> 19:57.863
Well, maybe Flaco's taking
on some new responsibilities.

19:59.432 --> 20:00.399
Yeah, I don't think so, man.

20:00.433 --> 20:01.834
Oh, come on, man.

20:01.867 --> 20:03.669
Uncuff me.
Uncuff me right now.

20:03.703 --> 20:05.504
- I can't, brother, I can't.
- Uncuff me right now.

20:05.538 --> 20:07.473
I let you live
long enough already!

20:07.506 --> 20:09.709
(Tuturro)
No, no, look, look,
go with me on this, man.

20:09.742 --> 20:12.111
Maybe he's got money for you,
maybe he's got a bullet, okay,

20:12.144 --> 20:13.245
but if you go in there
and get yourself shot up

20:13.279 --> 20:14.413
I got nothin' else.

20:14.447 --> 20:15.614
(Tuturro)
I'm trying to protect you.

20:15.648 --> 20:17.917
You're all I got, man.

20:21.053 --> 20:24.023
[dance music]

20:24.056 --> 20:32.098
♪ ♪

20:35.835 --> 20:38.504
[grunting]

20:48.481 --> 20:50.249
Hola.

20:53.552 --> 20:55.054
[yells]

20:55.087 --> 20:56.055
[gunshot]

20:56.088 --> 20:59.358
[people screaming]

21:04.330 --> 21:05.598
Hey! Yo, yo!

21:05.631 --> 21:07.266
Don't shoot, don't shoot!
It's me.

21:07.299 --> 21:10.169
Give me my money.
Huh?

21:10.202 --> 21:11.170
There was no money,
there was--

21:11.203 --> 21:12.538
Where's my goddamn money?

21:12.571 --> 21:15.107
There was no money.
There was bullets, okay?

21:15.141 --> 21:16.675
Put the gun down.

21:18.878 --> 21:20.513
Uncuff me.

21:20.546 --> 21:22.548
Uncuff me.
It's down.

21:25.317 --> 21:28.487
[handcuffs clinking]

21:30.823 --> 21:32.424
Look, man,
you want your money?

21:32.458 --> 21:35.861
You're gonna need my help
to get it.

21:35.895 --> 21:38.731
I'm going down there
to get Lucia.

21:38.764 --> 21:41.133
You wanna run,
I ain't gonna stop you.

21:41.167 --> 21:44.436
But you want your money?

21:44.470 --> 21:46.605
Yeah, I'm in.
I'm in.

21:46.639 --> 21:49.608
[rap music]

21:49.642 --> 21:57.917
♪ ♪

21:57.950 --> 22:01.954
[women squealing]

22:11.163 --> 22:19.171
♪ ♪

22:23.175 --> 22:24.910
[breathing slowly]

22:32.218 --> 22:34.553
You are 50 shades
of messed up, ain't you?

22:34.587 --> 22:35.921
I'm fine.

22:35.955 --> 22:37.590
Yeah, right.
Picture of health.

22:37.623 --> 22:40.259
I'm going to see
the Bureau physician.

22:40.292 --> 22:44.330
I just needed to cut the edge
so I can get cleared for action.

22:44.363 --> 22:46.031
My brother,
I just watched you struggle

22:46.065 --> 22:47.533
with a flight of stairs.

22:47.566 --> 22:50.202
I don't know if action's
gonna be in your portfolio.

22:50.236 --> 22:52.705
Jakes, I was dead
for six minutes.

22:52.738 --> 22:54.673
If I was sent back,
I was sent back for a reason,

22:54.707 --> 22:57.009
and it wasn't to enjoy
an extended convalescence.

22:57.042 --> 22:59.812
Whoa, did you just say
you were "sent back"?

22:59.845 --> 23:01.580
You know what I mean.

23:01.614 --> 23:02.581
Okay, listen.

23:02.615 --> 23:05.117
If I were you,
I'd take it easy.

23:05.150 --> 23:06.385
Instead, you're you,

23:06.418 --> 23:08.854
and you want to hurry your
sick ass back to active duty.

23:08.888 --> 23:10.189
Fine, I get that.

23:10.222 --> 23:13.092
My advice, when you
go in for your physical,

23:13.125 --> 23:14.593
maybe leave out
the noise about

23:14.627 --> 23:16.896
mission from God.

23:16.929 --> 23:19.164
Go with, um...

23:19.198 --> 23:21.066
"Everything's peachy."

23:22.868 --> 23:26.472
Yeah.

23:26.505 --> 23:28.507
"Everything's peachy."

23:28.540 --> 23:30.943
[rock music]

23:30.976 --> 23:32.511
[exhales]

23:32.544 --> 23:35.447
You're collecting battle scars
at a nifty clip.

23:35.481 --> 23:38.083
Breathe.

23:38.117 --> 23:40.753
Some people would say you're
lucky to survive all this.

23:40.786 --> 23:42.121
Breathe.

23:42.154 --> 23:43.822
[exhales]

23:43.856 --> 23:45.858
Personally, I think
the luckiest folks are

23:45.891 --> 23:48.560
the ones who avoid
scars altogether.

23:48.594 --> 23:50.496
Lungs sound good.

23:50.529 --> 23:52.665
You were out for
quite awhile.

23:52.698 --> 23:54.800
How's the head?
Any memory loss,

23:54.833 --> 23:56.535
headaches,
speech dysfunction?

23:56.568 --> 23:59.338
No, everything's...peachy.
[chuckles]

23:59.371 --> 24:01.440
- How's the pain?
- Manageable.

24:01.473 --> 24:03.208
You've been taking
the oxycodone?

24:03.242 --> 24:04.910
As necessary.

24:04.944 --> 24:06.912
Well, you're here,
you're moving,

24:06.946 --> 24:10.883
and if you're comfortable with
the ten pills you've got left,

24:10.916 --> 24:13.085
I'm comfortable
signing off on you.

24:13.118 --> 24:15.454
Maybe put me down
for one refill?

24:15.487 --> 24:17.289
In case the pain
flares up?

24:17.323 --> 24:19.391
Well, I can issue
another prescription,

24:19.425 --> 24:21.193
but not if I'm
clearing you for duty.

24:21.226 --> 24:22.728
If you think you need
more medication--

24:22.761 --> 24:26.498
No. No, I-I'm good
with what I got.

24:26.532 --> 24:28.200
Let's get me
in the field.

24:28.233 --> 24:30.970
[door clattering]

24:31.003 --> 24:33.405
(Ari)
So anyway, the business is
international.

24:33.439 --> 24:34.974
My uncle and Martun--

24:35.007 --> 24:36.608
you know
Martun Sarkissian, yes?

24:36.642 --> 24:37.843
I know of him.

24:37.876 --> 24:39.345
In my uncle,
they have a buyer

24:39.378 --> 24:42.982
for whatever computer chip is in
surface to air missiles.

24:43.015 --> 24:45.217
The chip is worth
more than the payload.

24:45.250 --> 24:46.752
It's looney tunes.

24:46.785 --> 24:49.922
This is what our jogging friend
signed for over on the bridge?

24:51.090 --> 24:53.392
The fat man is a billionaire.

24:53.425 --> 24:56.328
Chester Cheeto,
king of the computer chip.

24:56.362 --> 24:58.530
Shoulda called him Doritos.

24:59.565 --> 25:01.467
Ah, because it's a chip.

25:01.500 --> 25:04.870
[laughs]
That's good, Guy.

25:04.903 --> 25:06.772
You're pretty funny.

25:06.805 --> 25:10.109
But how does a man let himself
get so fat, huh?

25:10.142 --> 25:13.045
For me, I could not.
It's repulsive.

25:13.078 --> 25:14.680
(Ari)
I would hire a trainer

25:14.713 --> 25:17.449
or get a lapband.

25:17.483 --> 25:20.619
My hairdresser,
she got the lapband.

25:20.652 --> 25:22.988
She lost like 40 pounds
right off the bat.

25:23.022 --> 25:26.025
She looks great.
I almost tried to screw her.

25:26.058 --> 25:28.560
Do you know anyone
who had the lapband?

25:31.196 --> 25:32.598
(Ari)
Are you listening to me, Guy?

25:32.631 --> 25:34.700
[gun fires]

25:34.733 --> 25:37.302
(woman)
Ari!

25:37.336 --> 25:38.904
Aw, shit.

25:40.272 --> 25:42.508
Ari, where are you?

25:43.575 --> 25:45.077
Stay here, Guy.
Don't move.

25:46.111 --> 25:47.813
No problem.

25:47.846 --> 25:49.515
Ari!

25:49.548 --> 25:52.785
Layla, baby,
you can't be here.

25:52.818 --> 25:53.786
What choice did I have?

25:53.819 --> 25:54.887
I've been calling Colby
for days.

25:54.920 --> 25:56.255
Where have you been?

25:56.288 --> 25:57.923
Colby's not on payroll anymore.
He's moved on.

25:57.956 --> 25:59.091
(Layla)
What do you mean, moved on?

25:59.124 --> 26:00.092
Is he dead?

26:00.125 --> 26:01.427
(Ari)
No, he has left.

26:01.460 --> 26:02.828
Like you need
to be doing, okay?

26:02.861 --> 26:04.163
You can't keep
ignoring me.

26:04.196 --> 26:05.397
Baby...

26:05.431 --> 26:06.398
Come here.

26:06.432 --> 26:07.933
You're so freaking beautiful,

26:07.966 --> 26:09.034
I want to be with you
all the time.

26:09.068 --> 26:11.970
But if your father find out,
I'm a dead man.

26:12.004 --> 26:13.338
So, Layla, please,

26:13.372 --> 26:16.275
go home,
and I'll call you.

26:16.308 --> 26:17.276
(Layla)
Promise?

26:17.309 --> 26:19.011
I promise.

26:25.084 --> 26:26.952
[door slams]

26:30.823 --> 26:32.691
How much of that
you catch?

26:32.724 --> 26:34.126
Huh? Oh, none of it.

26:35.761 --> 26:39.398
Bullshit, Guy.
You're a bad liar.

26:41.400 --> 26:43.335
That's a...pretty girl.

26:43.368 --> 26:44.603
Layla, is it?

26:44.636 --> 26:47.873
I swear to God,
she is a freaking child.

26:47.906 --> 26:50.042
I had Colby running
interference for me,

26:50.075 --> 26:54.413
but now I think maybe I want
you to take care of her.

26:54.446 --> 26:57.282
Uh...
like, take care of her?

26:57.316 --> 27:00.152
No, Guy, that's
Martun Sarkissian's daughter.

27:00.185 --> 27:02.621
I mean, get rooms,
field phone calls.

27:02.654 --> 27:03.722
I totally get it.

27:03.755 --> 27:05.657
Just help you keep
your nose clean, right?

27:05.691 --> 27:08.127
- Yes, take care of her.
- Can do.

27:08.160 --> 27:11.163
It's a lot of risk
for a piece of ass, but...

27:13.499 --> 27:15.968
What a sweet piece of ass.

27:18.137 --> 27:20.639
Anyway...

27:22.407 --> 27:24.910
She'll be going to
Stanford University

27:24.943 --> 27:26.345
at the end of the summer.

27:26.378 --> 27:27.813
(Ari)
She'll pledge a sorority,

27:27.846 --> 27:30.048
find a fraternity boyfriend.

27:30.082 --> 27:32.084
Not my problem anymore.

27:32.117 --> 27:33.385
You want a drink?

27:33.418 --> 27:36.688
Uh, I'd love to,
but I've got other plans.

27:36.722 --> 27:39.691
[rock music]

27:39.725 --> 27:45.864
♪ ♪

27:45.898 --> 27:48.901
[phone rings]

27:50.369 --> 27:53.005
Yo, this is like
a $500 bottle of wine.

27:53.038 --> 27:54.072
(Charlie)
Yeah, I know what it is.

27:54.106 --> 27:55.607
Paige can't leave me alone here

27:55.641 --> 27:57.042
with a bunch of
undersexed silver backs.

27:57.075 --> 27:58.410
- Yeah?
- What's the occasion?

27:58.443 --> 28:00.812
Charlie's of the belief
that she can get Paige to stay

28:00.846 --> 28:02.047
with a little family dinner.

28:02.080 --> 28:04.516
Uh-huh.
Well, that would convince me.

28:04.550 --> 28:06.351
(Mike)
What happened with Ari?

28:06.385 --> 28:08.487
You were right.
Plan didn't end well.

28:08.520 --> 28:09.922
So what's next?

28:09.955 --> 28:11.957
(Charlie) All right, thanks.
- New plan.

28:11.990 --> 28:14.226
Bad news,
Amber can't tag Germaine.

28:14.259 --> 28:17.029
Good news, there's a guy down
in the Everglades who can.

28:17.062 --> 28:18.363
- Florida?
- Yeah.

28:18.397 --> 28:20.632
Me and Amber are gonna go down
there, big bag of money,

28:20.666 --> 28:21.833
get in there with 'im,

28:21.867 --> 28:23.802
eventually ask him
to clean our profits.

28:23.835 --> 28:26.772
Uh-huh.
Did you say Amber and you?

28:26.805 --> 28:27.873
That's how it works.

28:27.906 --> 28:29.041
Right.

28:29.074 --> 28:30.709
- You're pregnant.
- No shit.

28:30.742 --> 28:32.578
The Bureau's taking me off
the field in eight weeks.

28:32.611 --> 28:33.812
What, Paul?

28:33.845 --> 28:35.280
Amber nearly got you killed,

28:35.314 --> 28:37.382
and now you want to run
a long-term drug op with her

28:37.416 --> 28:38.383
down in the swamps?

28:38.417 --> 28:40.586
Yeah, this was
your idea, remember?

28:40.619 --> 28:41.954
- Look, it's not happening.
- Oh, yes, it is.

28:41.987 --> 28:43.589
Hey, why don't we just have
some drinks, tell some--

28:43.622 --> 28:44.656
(Charlie)
You're not gonna tell me what
I'm gonna do--

28:44.690 --> 28:45.924
You almost lost the baby
once, Charlie.

28:45.958 --> 28:47.859
No shit, that's why I
want to get 'em now.

28:47.893 --> 28:49.394
If you so much as
step foot on a bird,

28:49.428 --> 28:50.596
I'll have you on
maternity leave

28:50.629 --> 28:52.631
before you push back
from the gate.

28:52.664 --> 28:53.632
Look, you're a mom now.

28:53.665 --> 28:54.800
Okay?
Act like it.

28:54.833 --> 28:56.501
You want to get Germaine?

28:56.535 --> 28:58.270
Find another way.

29:02.074 --> 29:04.343
I'm gonna go pack.

29:14.319 --> 29:22.327
♪ ♪

29:39.311 --> 29:41.480
Things had gotten violent.

29:41.513 --> 29:43.915
It was untenable.

29:43.949 --> 29:47.486
Sulla was...
frustrated.

29:47.519 --> 29:51.123
(Mike)
I think he felt impotent.

29:51.156 --> 29:52.991
And Lina...

29:53.025 --> 29:56.928
She bit him, actually.

29:56.962 --> 29:59.598
She was a fighter.

29:59.631 --> 30:01.233
I told him we were leaving.

30:01.266 --> 30:03.235
He said no.
I said yes.

30:04.936 --> 30:07.639
Lena was scared, but...

30:07.673 --> 30:10.142
We started for the door.

30:12.911 --> 30:14.279
He was on her so fast.

30:14.313 --> 30:16.315
I...

30:17.449 --> 30:20.018
I didn't even have
time to react.

30:24.656 --> 30:27.392
Everything we'd done...

30:27.426 --> 30:30.429
I just couldn't
fathom wasting it.

30:31.530 --> 30:35.100
So I committed
a selfish act.

30:35.133 --> 30:38.403
And I still see Lina
in my dreams.

30:47.512 --> 30:50.115
Don't leave, Paige.

30:57.589 --> 31:00.158
You're lucky,
you know that?

31:00.192 --> 31:01.326
You see her in your dreams,

31:01.360 --> 31:03.829
but when you wake up,

31:03.862 --> 31:06.198
she's gone.

31:08.033 --> 31:10.235
I don't have that luxury.

31:12.371 --> 31:13.505
You...

31:13.538 --> 31:16.441
this goddamn medal,
is a constant reminder

31:16.475 --> 31:18.510
of what I did wrong.

31:22.347 --> 31:23.582
Why don't you
let it be a reminder

31:23.615 --> 31:25.484
of what you did right?

31:28.920 --> 31:32.424
[sobbing]

31:36.194 --> 31:40.232
[gates opening]

31:43.468 --> 31:45.470
[man speaking Spanish]

31:47.439 --> 31:49.441
[man speaking Spanish]

31:56.715 --> 31:57.682
[muffled grunting]

31:57.716 --> 32:01.186
[struggling]

32:01.219 --> 32:04.055
(Tuturro)
[speaking Spanish]

32:05.490 --> 32:07.225
Get on your knees.

32:14.132 --> 32:15.634
Lucia.

32:16.668 --> 32:18.203
(Tuturro)
Lucia.

32:18.236 --> 32:19.571
Hey, hey, it's me, it's me,
it's me, it's me.

32:20.705 --> 32:22.140
Johnny.

32:25.110 --> 32:27.946
Let's go.

32:27.979 --> 32:29.114
He's right.
We gotta go, okay?

32:29.147 --> 32:30.115
There's a Range Rover
in the driveway.

32:30.148 --> 32:31.316
I've gotta get you
out of here.

32:31.349 --> 32:33.118
We're not done here yet.
You got your girl.

32:33.151 --> 32:34.953
I get my money.
That was the deal.

32:34.986 --> 32:37.122
That's my deal,
you piece of shit.

32:39.324 --> 32:41.726
You tried to kill my friends.
You think I'm gonna help you?

32:41.760 --> 32:42.961
You want your money?

32:42.994 --> 32:44.796
Go wake up Carlito.
See if he's feeling generous.

32:44.830 --> 32:46.131
- But if I was you--
- Johnny...

32:46.164 --> 32:47.132
- I'd run...
- Johnny, Johnny...

32:47.165 --> 32:48.467
And be happy
I'm not doing that shit

32:48.500 --> 32:49.434
with a hollow point in my gun.

32:49.468 --> 32:50.869
- Johnny!
- What?

32:50.902 --> 32:52.304
- Look, mija, we gotta go, okay?
- We can't leave.

32:52.337 --> 32:54.940
My brother owns everything
from here to the border.

32:56.708 --> 32:58.777
Now why don't you just
listen to your girlfriend?

32:58.810 --> 33:02.280
If he's alive,
we won't make it ten miles.

33:05.116 --> 33:07.052
[safety clicks]

33:07.085 --> 33:10.055
[dramatic music]

33:10.088 --> 33:17.028
♪ ♪

33:20.632 --> 33:22.601
[car engine shuts off]

33:25.804 --> 33:27.138
Hey.

33:28.206 --> 33:29.841
You don't have to do this.

33:29.875 --> 33:31.409
I'm serious, Charlie.

33:31.443 --> 33:34.546
You say one word,
and we're outta here.

33:34.579 --> 33:36.748
Something I gotta do.

33:36.781 --> 33:38.450
Okay.

33:39.551 --> 33:42.354
But is it something that
you want to do?

33:44.623 --> 33:47.259
My nonna was a cardiologist.

33:47.292 --> 33:49.794
She worked till she was 74.

33:49.828 --> 33:51.062
It's ironic.

33:51.096 --> 33:54.466
It took two heart attacks
for her to retire.

33:54.499 --> 33:56.368
She had pensions,
savings, all that,

33:56.401 --> 33:58.336
but she kept going back to work
'cause she said,

33:58.370 --> 34:02.741
when people looked at her
they saw a doctor.

34:04.676 --> 34:10.515
Like they--they saw someone
they respected, and...

34:10.549 --> 34:13.952
Second she hung up
that white coat,

34:13.985 --> 34:16.488
she was just an old lady.

34:18.590 --> 34:21.192
You ask me what I want.
That's the question.

34:21.226 --> 34:23.128
Because...

34:24.896 --> 34:28.600
Down one path, I'm Charlie
DeMarco, federal agent.

34:30.569 --> 34:34.706
And down another path,
I'm Charlie DeMarco, single mom.

34:36.608 --> 34:38.009
And you know,
what Paul said, it--

34:38.043 --> 34:41.346
I may not like it,
but...

34:41.379 --> 34:44.015
He's not wrong.

34:47.752 --> 34:50.789
It's just a choice
I have to make, you know?

34:53.425 --> 34:55.894
And you're sure
about this?

34:55.927 --> 35:00.265
No, Paige, I'm not sure
of anything anymore.

35:00.298 --> 35:03.068
(Charlie)
It's just one of those things,
man.

35:03.101 --> 35:06.037
Life hands them to you
all the time.

35:06.071 --> 35:09.674
You got a steaming heap of
shit in your right hand,

35:09.708 --> 35:11.409
and a steaming heap of
shit in your left,

35:11.443 --> 35:13.044
and you look at both
and you can't tell

35:13.078 --> 35:14.346
one bad hand
from the other.

35:16.982 --> 35:19.417
(Charlie)
You ask me, an exceptional hero?

35:19.451 --> 35:22.988
That's when you know both hands
are shit and you choose anyway.

35:26.825 --> 35:28.994
And then you spend
the rest of forever

35:29.027 --> 35:31.396
getting used to the smell.

35:42.807 --> 35:44.809
[classical music]

35:44.843 --> 35:46.344
[gun cocks]

35:46.378 --> 35:48.713
(Sid)
Get up. Slowly.

35:48.747 --> 35:49.981
What is this?

35:50.015 --> 35:51.449
I want you to take me to
your safe right now

35:51.483 --> 35:53.585
and I want you
to pay me my money.

35:53.618 --> 35:54.886
Johnny...

35:54.919 --> 35:57.522
(Tuturro)
I'd pay the man.

35:57.555 --> 35:59.958
If I die, my sister dies.
You know this.

35:59.991 --> 36:02.927
Nah. Not anymore.
Get up.

36:02.961 --> 36:04.129
Outta the goddamn bathtub.

36:09.367 --> 36:11.569
I gave Flaco $900,000.

36:11.603 --> 36:13.338
I'm taking it you never
saw any of this?

36:13.371 --> 36:14.639
(Tuturro)
There was no money.

36:14.673 --> 36:16.474
He shot at us.

36:16.508 --> 36:18.810
(Carlito)
Oh, he shot at you?
Verdad?

36:18.843 --> 36:21.146
Flaco?
Hmm.

36:21.179 --> 36:22.781
And you saw this?

36:24.249 --> 36:26.251
(Carlito)
Yeah, I don't blame you,
you know.

36:26.284 --> 36:30.055
He's a practiced liar, Johnny.

36:30.088 --> 36:32.957
But you know I'm telling
the truth, right?

36:34.392 --> 36:36.795
It's too late anyway now.
Come on.

36:38.229 --> 36:39.264
Si.

36:47.372 --> 36:49.474
Let's go.
Open it.

36:51.142 --> 36:52.143
[door beeps]

37:01.052 --> 37:02.887
Take it and go.

37:02.921 --> 37:05.090
This...misunderstanding

37:05.123 --> 37:08.993
does not need to end
in bloodshed.

37:09.027 --> 37:10.795
[gunshots]

37:10.829 --> 37:16.234
[high-pitched ringing]

37:19.471 --> 37:23.108
[enraged grunting]

37:23.141 --> 37:24.876
[shouting]

37:27.712 --> 37:30.048
[loud punches]

37:30.081 --> 37:33.785
(Carlito)
[groans]

37:33.818 --> 37:35.186
(Lucia)
Johnny!

37:35.220 --> 37:38.189
- No!
- [indistinct shouting]

37:38.223 --> 37:39.257
(Tuturro)
Lucia!

37:39.290 --> 37:41.126
(Lucia)
Johnny!

37:43.962 --> 37:46.898
(Carlito)
[yells]

37:46.931 --> 37:48.133
(Sid)
[enraged groan]

37:48.433 --> 37:50.902
If I die, she dies.

37:54.239 --> 37:56.441
(Carlito)
Ahhh!

37:56.474 --> 37:58.843
[gunshots]

37:58.877 --> 38:01.446
[Carlito panting]
If I die, she dies.

38:13.825 --> 38:15.160
That's a good boy, Johnny.

38:53.464 --> 38:55.800
You know I'm supposed to
get a phone call

38:55.834 --> 38:58.837
before you go in there,
not after, right?

39:00.672 --> 39:03.808
Just take me home, Paul.

39:03.842 --> 39:06.678
This is supposed to be
a discussion, Charlie.

39:06.711 --> 39:08.079
This isn't what I meant
when I said--

39:08.112 --> 39:11.182
Do you even want
to be a father?

39:13.585 --> 39:16.888
Then let's just cut to the part
where you're relieved.

39:18.089 --> 39:21.259
You don't have to
grow up just yet.

39:25.330 --> 39:27.232
(woman)
DeMarco?

39:27.265 --> 39:28.233
[engine turning over]

39:28.266 --> 39:31.669
DeMarco.

39:31.703 --> 39:34.672
Catherine DeMarco?

39:34.706 --> 39:37.675
[blues music]

39:37.709 --> 39:45.717
♪ ♪

39:55.894 --> 39:59.063
[glass shattering]

39:59.097 --> 40:03.368
♪ ♪

40:03.401 --> 40:04.602
[metal door opening,
buzzing]

40:04.636 --> 40:12.644
♪ ♪

41:18.242 --> 41:20.545
[car accelerates]

41:23.614 --> 41:26.784
[glass shattering
and tires squealing]

41:31.255 --> 41:33.524
[hyperventilating]
Please somebody!

41:33.558 --> 41:35.059
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

41:35.093 --> 41:38.262
No!
[crying]

41:38.296 --> 41:41.299
No, please, somebody!
No, no, no, no, no, no!

42:06.791 --> 42:09.260
[dog barking]
